AWSServiceRoleForOrganizations Role created on each member account which allows to control member account using IAM user off master account.
OrganizationAccountAccessRole has full permission to manage member account. This role gives enough priviliges to 
Service Control policies (SCP) are attached to each member account.
You can enable service trust for another AWS service. When do that, it creates service linked-role. 

Policy Types:

SCP (service control policy)
tag policies

SCP: SCPs offer central control over the maximum available permissions for all accounts in your organization.


